+### noisy git wrapper
+
+A `git` wrapper on `PATH` may ignore `--quiet` and write progress to stdout.
+Since `antidote-script` emits the generated plugin script on stdout, that noise
+must not contaminate the script, while diagnostics are still surfaced on stderr.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { print "GIT-WRAPPER-STDOUT-NOISE"; mockgit "$@" }
+% rm -rf -- $ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser
+% antidote-script fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo/fakerepo.plugin.zsh"
+% rm -rf -- $ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser
+% ( setopt no_multios; antidote-script fakeuser/fakerepo 2>&1 >/dev/null ) | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+# antidote cloning fakeuser/fakerepo...
+GIT-WRAPPER-STDOUT-NOISE
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
+
